Adam Dolph is a Hungarian music addict, who started DJ-ing in 2009, after grabbing DJ Vadim's 'U Can't Learn Imaginashun' vinyl in a crowd, which was the first influence for him. After diving himself in the world of electronic music vinyls, he started his own weekly radio show called 'Bling Bling' to practice the art of mixing and invite local DJs, too.
In 2012, Adam was proposed in another radio show to play a set before Krueger & Pryus, founders of Ninjabreakz, Hungary's most important breakbeat promoter crew. He was instantly requested to play on their next A38 Boat party before Deekline. Since his debut act, he became a resident member of the Ninjas, and played with a wide range of international artists, such as Krafty Kuts, Stanton Warriors, Plump DJs, Nick Thayer, A-Skillz, Adam Freeland, Ed Solo, JFB, High Rankin, Pegboard Nerds, Lady Waks, Pixel Fist, Stickybuds, Marten Horger, Dancefloor Outlaws, Hedflux, Ludmilla, Anima Sound System, Jumo Daddy, Kid Panel and more.
Adam builds his mixes from a lot of different genres like breakbeat, bass, electro-house, trap and drum & bass music. Dates and more info available at his Facebook page.
